"So kid any last words." Quake asked, pointing Heater, who quickly
joined the fight down at Jagged. "No. I thought you might say some more
things you couldn't back up." he taunted. He tightened his finger, but
stopped at a deep voice. "Nooooo. He dosent need to back up his words. I
do it for him." a dark ominous voice said from behind.
Quake whirled around, but could only see half of a robot shrouded by
some sort of smoke. SLuglsinger jumped up from his seat. "Ohhh boy, this
is to much for me." he said frantically, jumping out of his seat, and
running out of the bar, joined by Caliburst. Slugslinger transformed,
and opened his cockpit, which Caliburst gracefully entered, as they sped
away from the conflict.

Meanwhile in the bar, Quake fired at the smoke cloud, only to miss the
robot, who slowly weaved out of the way of each shot. Quake screamed, as
Tiptop transformed into his gun mode, and landed in the other hand.
"Your gonna die Stranger." He threatened, filling the cloud with gun
fire. From behind the voice came again. "No one messes with a
Cybernight, and lives." the voice whispered, this time from behind
Quake. The room was to small, and was easily filling up with the smoke,
and making it hard for Quake to determine anything.
